Officers made the arrests after responding to a tip-off about random shootings after 10pm on Wednesday night in Lotus River. CAPE TOWN - Metro police officers have arrested five suspected gang members in Lotus River, Cape Town. Officers made the arrests after responding to a tip-off about random shootings after 10pm on Wednesday night. Metro Police spokesperson Zelda Martin said: “While patrolling the area, officers stopped a VW Golf and recovered a 9mm pistol and six rounds of ammunition, dagga and R1,330 in cash.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)